Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at TCF Center in Detroit, Michigan, praising the city's resilience in the face of challenges such as the pandemic. She thanked frontline workers, including healthcare workers and teachers, for their dedication and sacrifice. Harris emphasized the importance of getting vaccinated and urged people to spread accurate information about the vaccines. She highlighted the Delta variant as a serious threat and noted that virtually every person currently hospitalized or who has died from COVID-19 is unvaccinated. Harris encouraged everyone to get vaccinated to protect themselves and their communities. She ended her speech by calling for unity and resilience to overcome the pandemic.